Description: Neulogix Solutions is helping companies obtain value from their information.
Headquarters Regions: Southern US
Full Description: Neulogix Solutions is helping companies obtain value from their information.  They provide solutions that empower the right people with the right information at the right time so you can operate your plants more safely, securely, and efficiently. The effective and safe operation of a process facility is achieved with people, processes, and technology.  Information is the resource that integrates them all.  It is a corporate asset that must be created, protected, used, maintained and decommissioned just as physical assets.  Information is only as good as its accuracy, relevance, timeliness, availability, and authenticity.    They facilitate change.  Healthy engineering, operations, and maintenance organizations are always in flux due to market conditions or through pursuit of strategic goals.  Changes to people, processes, or technology can impact the relevance, quality, and safekeeping of the information. Lack of corresponding proactive changes to the information asset typically leads to a downward spiral of deteriorating information reliability. Wrong information is sometimes more dangerous than no information because it encourages unwarranted confidence.  On the other hand, loss of confidence in the information can lead to costly multiple validations.    They help their customers maximize the economic advantages of change by minimizing the degradation of the information asset in the organization.  Their teams bring multi-disciplinary talent together to help organize, protect, enhance and extract value from information.

Description: Much of tech is monetized by online advertising. Although a successful model for the tech companies.
Headquarters Regions: Greater Atlanta Area, East Coast, Southern US
Full Description: Much of tech is monetized by online advertising. Although a successful model for the tech companies, advertisers are finding the benefit-cost ratio questionable, but more importantly – its contributing to the broader problem of information overload to the consumer. The PDF deck shows that based on some research and deduction that the average human has learned to adapt to this and only absorb information selectively. Not only has the consumer’s marketing experience become increasingly negative, but our experience has also taught us that advertisers are less than happy with the results. The industry is ripe for change. RINC would like to reinvent itself and raise $3M to bring to market a smarter, game changing marketing/advertising model as outlined in the deck that: 1.	is a positive brand experience 2.	is absorbed by the consumer without the need for conscious engagement 3.	would be more inclined to be viral in nature, a notoriously elusive quality, as advertisers can attest to 4.    is scalable Tristan, Mark and Robert will be forming a team once capital has been raised, that have had over 70 years in business and have learned the industry’s shortcomings and have the experience to make change happen. As there are many stakeholders in the $600B advertising business willing to protect their status quo, the possibility of an early buyout should certainly be a factor to potential investor in RINC in how that might reduce their exposure to risk.

Full Description: Attorney Steven Snyder  of Snyder Law Firm specializes in helping clients with assisted reproductive technology (ART) law and estate planning matters and has been a practicing attorney in both areas for almost 30 years.  Estate planning has always been a large part of his practice, and he enjoys giving personal guidance to clients who are going through this sensitive, complex process.  Attorney Snyder completed one of the first surrogacy cases in Minnesota in the 1980s in which he successfully established the parentage of a German couple who had worked with a surrogate in Minnesota to have a child.  He has now completed this process for over 200 other intended parents and has made the ART law side of his practice his main focus.  He assists clients who require any type of third party assistance to build their family, including egg, sperm, or embryo donation and surrogacy.  His services include contract representation, medical insurance reviews, and completing any legal process necessary to ensure the intended parents are established as the sole parents of the child and are able to exercise this legal relationship from the moment of birth.  Please contact him at 763-420-6700 for a free consultation.

Full Description: Critica Books is a literary magazine founded by Mason Ewing Corp., the American holding company of Mason Ewing. The first issue was released in October 2022.  Critica Books is both traditional and modern, and is inspired by the spirit of the dialectic valued by ancient Rome’s orators and readers. Dialectic is the art of logical discussion to investigate the truth of an opionion or theory. During that time period, literature had a central place in the life of man.  Considered as the best way to convey moral values and principles,  and to attain wisdom, reading was recommended by the greatest thinkers and authors.  Similar to the Greeks and their great philosophers or fable writers (Aristotle, Plato, Phaedra, and Aesop)!  Critica Books is specialized in literary criticism of a wide variety of books and wants to help people discover remarkable books and talents. The magazine’s team are literary enthusiasts who want to unearth forgotten masterpieces, give their opinions on modern bestsellers and also unearth authors who deserve to be known.  Mason Ewing, President of MEC and creator of Critica Books, aims for this magazine to help develop children's critical thinking skills and give them a passion for reading.   When Mason was young, reading saved him by helping him to escape and dream.   In the future, Critica Books will bring together a community of journalists from all over the world and should become a reference in literary magazines.  The magazine will also create podcasts that will enrich the news articles and reviews.
